Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with resource allocation in cognitive radio systems, which is a networking issue. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper uses multi-agent reinforcement learning (MARL) in the framework of Q-learning, which is a subfield of AI. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses Q-learning, which is a machine learning algorithm. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper deals with the dynamics of the Q-learning algorithm and provides a convergence analysis, which is related to systems and control. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with channel selection in cognitive radio systems, which is related to information theory.
